.Dd June 26, 2026
.Dt FSREFSINFO 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm fsrefsinfo
.Nd determines information about a Resiliant File System (ReFS) volume
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm fsrefsinfo
.Op Fl hvV
.Ar source
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm fsrefsinfo
is a utility to determine information about a Resiliant File System (ReFS) \
volume
.Pp
.Nm fsrefsinfo
is part of the
.Nm libfsrefs
package.
.Nm libfsrefs
is a library to access the Resiliant File System (ReFS) format
.Pp
.Ar source
is the source volume.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl h
shows this help
.It Fl v
verbose output to stderr
.It Fl V
print version
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
None
.Sh FILES
None
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal
# fsrefsinfo /dev/sda1
fsrefsinfo 20260626
.sp
Resiliant File System (ReFS) volume information:
.sp
Volume information:
	Name				: Test Volume
	Version				: 1.1
	Serial number			: bf790b1be6690b15
	Bytes per sector		: 512
	Cluster block size		: 65536
.sp
.Ed
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
Errors, verbose and debug output are printed to stderr when verbose output \
\-v is enabled.
Verbose and debug output are only printed when enabled at compilation.
